==English==
===Etymology===
Latin vacill re, vacill t-, ''to waver''.

===Intransitive Verb===
'''vac·il·late''' (vacillated, vacillating, vacillates)

#To [[sway]] from one side to the other; [[oscillate]]. 
#To swing [[indecisively]] from one course of action or opinion to another. ('''synonym''': [[hesitation]])
#*'''2004:''' [[w: Chris Wallace (journalist)|Chris Wallace]], ''Character:  Profiles in Presidential Courage''
#*:On the streets of Berlin, Ruth and her compatriots '''vacillated''' "between hope and despair."  
#To be changeable or [[inconsistent]] in speech or action.

